def: Not admitting of being vitrified, or converted into glass.Kirwan.

The work done by a steam engine or other prime mover whenworking. Load line, or Load water line (Naut.), the line on theoutside of a vessel indicating the depth to which it sinks in thewater when loaded.
A genus of trees, called also the silkcotton tree; also, a treeof the genus Bombax.
A common American minnow (Fundulus majalis). See Minnow.
Capable of being extricated. Sir W. Jones.
To hide in, or as in, a cave or recess. "Do but encaveyourself." Shak.
